  "texts": [
    "These datasets may be more manageable in size and easier to work with, providing meaningful insights without the same level of computational demands as big data analysis.As shown in Fig. 8, several problems exist in eHealth based IoT, including:• Keeping data secure and private is the most challenging task since the daily data acquired is so huge [41].",
    "• Overusing medical devices might generate network congestion and poor data transfer speeds.Obtaining IoT devices remains a huge challenge [6].",
    "Blockchain technology presents a solution to these issues, and we will explore the different types of blockchains and their features in the next section.",
    "Additionally, we will discuss the advantages of using blockchain in healthcare and the consensus methods that are employed in healthcare.",
    "Blockchain technologyThe term ''Blockchain'' was first coined by [42] to describe the technology behind the digital currency Bitcoin."
  ]
}